"Quod J.P., Barrère A., Chabanet P., Durville P., Nicet J.B., Garnier R.","The status of the coral reefs of French Scattered Islands in the Indian Ocean [La situation des récifs coralliens des Îles Éparses Françaises de l'Ocean Indien]",2007,"Revue d'Ecologie (La Terre et la Vie)","62","1",,"3","16",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34347329303&partnerID=40&md5=9460f6ea7318f2dd4c916ed0f6720ebe","ARVAM, Technopole de la Réunion, 3 rue Henri Cornu, F-97490 Sainte-Clotilde, France; IRD Nouméa, BP A5, Nouméa; Aquarium de la Réunion, Port de Plaisance, F-97434 Saint-Gilles-les Bains, Reunion; PARETO, 15 Impasse Hyménées, F-97438 Sainte-Marie","Quod, J.P., ARVAM, Technopole de la Réunion, 3 rue Henri Cornu, F-97490 Sainte-Clotilde, France; Barrère, A., ARVAM, Technopole de la Réunion, 3 rue Henri Cornu, F-97490 Sainte-Clotilde, France; Chabanet, P., IRD Nouméa, BP A5, Nouméa; Durville, P., Aquarium de la Réunion, Port de Plaisance, F-97434 Saint-Gilles-les Bains, Reunion; Nicet, J.B., PARETO, 15 Impasse Hyménées, F-97438 Sainte-Marie; Garnier, R., PARETO, 15 Impasse Hyménées, F-97438 Sainte-Marie","Together with La Réunion and Mayotte Islands, Scattered Islands make up French Indian Ocean Territories (FIOT) which all possess highly ecologically sensitive natural habitats of major value for migrant species (turtles, seabirds, mammals). As a contribution to the national action plan of IFRECOR (French initiative on coral reefs) we set up during the period 2002-2005 a survey and monitoring program in order to increase the knowledge of the still poorly known coral reefs of these islands scattered from North to South in the Mozambique Channel and in central Indian Ocean. Results were particularly focused on the geomorphological mapping of shallow marine habitats and on a structural and functional approach of fish, coral and mollusc communities. Additional approaches with rapid assessment methods remained non exhaustive but nevertheless allow a first integrated diagnosis of the patrimonial value of the coral sanctuaries of Scattered Islands and to propose decision-making tools for identifying applied and fundamental axes of research as well as actions of monitoring adapted particularly to vulnerability factors and global warming.",,"biological survey; coral; coral reef; fish; geomorphological mapping; global warming; habitat management; island; migratory species; mollusc; monitoring; shallow water; Eurasia; Europe; France; Indian Ocean; Indian Ocean islands; Mascarene Islands; Mayotte; Mozambique Channel; Reunion; Western Europe; Anthozoa; Mammalia; Mollusca; Testudines",,,,,,"AHAMADA, S., BIJOUX, J., BIGOT, L., CAUVIN, B., KOONJUL, M., MAHARAVO, J., MEUNIER, S., PIERRE-LOUIS, R., Status of the coral reefs of the South-West Indian ocean island states (2004) Status of coral reefs of the world, pp. 189-211. , Pp, C. Wilkinson ed, GCRMN, AIMS Townsville, Australie; AIELLO, R.L., Successes and failures of global reef management (1996) Reef Tourism 2005, , Cairns; ALLEN, G.R., WERNER, T.B., Coral Reef fish assessment in the coral triangle of southeastern Asia (2002) Env. Biol. Fish, 65, pp. 209-214; ANDREFOUET, S., KRAMER, P., TORRES- PULLIZA, D., JOYCE, K.E., HOCHBERG, E.J., GARCA-PEREZ, R., MUMBY, P.J., RIEGL, B., YAMANO, H, WHITE, W.H., ZUBIA, M., BROCK, J.C., PHINN, S.R., NASEER, A., HATCHER, B.G. & MULLER-KARGER, F.E. (2003). - Multi-sites evaluation of IKONOS data for classification of tropical coral reef environments. Remote Sensing of Environment, 88:128-143ANDREFOUET, S., CHAUVIN, C., SPREGGINS, S., TORRES-PULLIZA, D., KRANENBURG, C., (2005) Atlas des récifs coralliens de Polynésie Française, , Centre IRD de Nouméa; ANDREFOUET, S., TORRES-PULLIZA, D., Atlas des récifs coralliens de Nouvelle- Calédonie (2004) IFRECOR Nouvelle-Calédonie, , IRD, Nouméa; BARTSCH, I., Halacaridae (Acari) aus dem Kanal von Moçambique (1981) Cah. Biol. Mar, 22, pp. 35-63; BATTISTINI, R., La morphologie de l'île d'Europa (1966) Mém. Mus. N